   <abstract>Charles McClung built Kingston Pike in 1792. He also commissioned the first home to be built along the Pike, which he named "Statesview." Over the years, other wealthy Knoxvillians built more homes along the road, including Drury P. Armstrong's "Crescent Bend" (1832), Robert H. Armstrong's "Bleak House" (1856), and J.E. Lutz's "Westwood" (1890). Although the Pike has been heavily developed during the 20th century, some portions retain their original residential character.</abstract>
